Here are all the relevant locations where the extension calls the pause API endpoint:

---

### 1. API Method Definition — `backendClient.ts`

**File:** `/Users/hobo/Projects/AgentLog/packages/vscode-extension/src/client/backendClient.ts`
**Lines 843–856**

```typescript
async pauseTrace(traceId: string): Promise<unknown> {
  const resp = await this.request<ApiResponse<unknown>>(
    "POST",
    `/api/traces/${encodeURIComponent(traceId)}/pause`,
  );
  if (!resp.success) {
    throw new BackendApiError(
      200,
      `/api/traces/${traceId}/pause`,
      resp.error ?? "暂停 trace 失败",
    );
  }
  return resp.data;
}
```

This is where the HTTP call is constructed. It issues a `POST` to `/api/traces/:id/pause`, throwing a `BackendApiError` if the response indicates failure.

For completeness, the companion `resumeFromPause` method is immediately below at **lines 861–874**, hitting `POST /api/traces/:id/resume-from-pause`.

---

### 2. Command Registration & Invocation — `extension.ts`

**File:** `/Users/hobo/Projects/AgentLog/packages/vscode-extension/src/extension.ts`
**Lines 2180–2202**

```typescript
register("agentlog.pauseTrace", async (item: unknown) => {
  let traceId: string | undefined;

  if (item instanceof TraceItem) {
    traceId = item.trace.id;
  }

  if (!traceId) {
    vscode.window.showErrorMessage("无法解析 Trace ID");
    return;
  }

  try {
    const client = getBackendClient();
    await client.pauseTrace(traceId);   // <-- calls the API method above
    traceTreeProvider.refresh();
    vscode.window.showInformationMessage("✅ Trace 已暂停");
  } catch (err) {
    vscode.window.showErrorMessage(
      `暂停失败：${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`,
    );
  }
});
```

This registers the `agentlog.pauseTrace` VS Code command. When triggered (e.g. from the tree view context menu on a `TraceItem`), it extracts the trace ID, calls `client.pauseTrace(traceId)`, and refreshes the tree view on success.

